==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hypogene
<hw>Hyp"o*gene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hypo-</ets> + the root of Gr. <grk>gi`gnesqai</grk> to be born: cf.
F. <ets>hypog⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Formed or
crystallized at depths beneath the earth's surface; -- said of granite,
gneiss, and other rocks, whose crystallization is believed of have taken
place beneath a great thickness of overlying rocks. Opposed to
<contr>epigene</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypogeous</ent>⟦br⟧
